LIMPOPO communities are still reeling from shock following three separate domestic disputes that turned into horror killings on Saturday. In Mokwakwaila Village, a 49-year-old man was burnt to death in his house at about 3.45pm after a domestic dispute.The man attempted to burn his children and himself after he had severely assaulted his wife, but luckily the children were removed. His wife was rescued by community members and rushed to hospital. The man burnt to death.His car also went up in flames. Limpopo police spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said a case of arson has been opened.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjss54UwbG8rntbeQ7WnaZheSZ3UKu6S8uADeJYEUKcxg6SOFKwsmbufAGlEPtkOdTYE8-nZNLJfCGVXlTHAJo6W_I3rG6YB4aR3mUBOfdr4tmDmyGO9X4V-Jz8IuTHZFktAiaWrEvPTnvRuYHxQgrNf9rsHMuQzUD6_h9a-KZ7cdDT5s0sVaZ-HcRl0EKb5eU0rYcsd4EP7LLirbWwsUzk_aSST8LPT7yOHcci8kVjw9oE_NKZAkKWEuIx8kyyxujmnLwSPOeM5SmCI65P1uIvGvgovkVOw\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzGux33tXjvbbEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
